            <title>[MNG-1895] Dependencies in two paths are not added to resolution when scope needs to be updated in the nearest  due to any of nearest parents</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MNG-1895</link>
                <project id="12316922" key="MNG">Maven (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;scopes are not correctly calculated for this case&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;my pom: a compile, b test&lt;br/&gt;
a: c compile, d compile&lt;br/&gt;
b: d compile&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;then d ends in test scope because d is closer to my project through the path b-d&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think scope importance should also be taken into account&lt;/p&gt;</description>
